member.name: FILE_OBJECTID_BUFFER
member.summary: Contains an object identifier and user-defined metadata associated with the object identifier.

member.name: FILE_OBJECTID_BUFFER.ObjectId
member.summary: The identifier that uniquely identifies the file or directory within the volume on which it resides.

member.name: FILE_OBJECTID_BUFFER.DUMMYUNIONNAME.DUMMYSTRUCTNAME.BirthVolumeId
member.summary: The identifier of the volume on which the object resided when the object identifier was created, or zero if the volume had no object identifier at that time. After copy operations, move operations, or other file operations, this may not be the same as the object identifier of the volume on which the object presently resides.

member.name: FILE_OBJECTID_BUFFER.DUMMYUNIONNAME.DUMMYSTRUCTNAME.BirthObjectId
member.summary: The object identifier of the object at the time it was created. After copy operations, move operations, or other file operations, this may not be the same as the ObjectId member at present.

member.name: FILE_OBJECTID_BUFFER.DUMMYUNIONNAME.ExtendedInfo
member.summary: User-defined extended data to be set with FSCTL_SET_OBJECT_ID_EXTENDED. Use this data as an alternative to the BirthVolumeId, BirthObjectId, and DomainId members.
